Marked KNOWNBUG: triggers an upstream cbmc invariant failure in
goto_check_c.cpp::bounds_check_index. The hand-written main.c uses
__CPROVER_bool var1[101] (an array of 101 1-bit elements) inside a
struct, indexed by a signed int. cbmc's build_object_descriptor_rec
returns a typeless ID_unknown offset because the element size is
sub-byte, and the lower-bound check then calls
from_integer(0, ode.offset().type()) on the empty type and aborts.
The combination (sub-byte element + struct member + signed index) is
not exercised by upstream cbmc's own tests. hw-cbmc's gen_interface
generates the same bit-vector as a single __CPROVER_bitvector[101]
field, which would side-step the bug; revisit this test when the
upstream cbmc bug is fixed or the test is rewritten to that form.
